  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) mandates\n\n3. Key Compliance Measures\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Enhanced screening for high-risk transactions\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Targeted Sectors\n- Banking\n- Financial services\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Real estate\n- Gambling industries\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income through complex financial transactions.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering prevention?",
